<TITLE> Seven injured in BCL factional clash at CUET </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com)  Some seven cadres of Bangladesh Chhatra Leaguethe student front of ruling Awami Leaguewere injured in a clash between two rival factions on Tuesday night. The clash erupted while paying tributes to the martyrs at Chittagong University of Engineering and Technology (CUET). The injured students were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital and Rauzan Upazila health complex. One of the injured was identified as Sujon, 23. Officer-in-charge of Rauzan Police Station Nikhil Mondol told bdnews24.com the clash erupted over which of the two factions would lay wreaths the Shaeed Minar at 12:01am. Police arrived at the scene within 10-15 minutes and took the situation under control. Additional police forces were deployed in the campus, he added. A CUET teacher who wanted not to be quoted said currently the two factions are active in campus politics -- one 'Ador group' backed by Fazle Karim MP from Rauzan and another 'Abdul Gani group' which has the support of state minister for environment Hassan Mahmud. bdnews2
